is it crazy to feel sad when you find out that you have miscarried when you were only weeks along i go back and forth thinking people are gonna think im crazy for being so sad today and then going back to thinking that it would be weird if i wasn t sad about it i cry thinking about losing it even tho it didn t have a heart that was beating yet do others go thru these feelings are people gonna think i m a wack a do if i am upset about a miscarriage so soon into the pregnancy are my hormones all out of wack now too is that why im so upset positive pregnancy test on sat july th then stopped having any pregnancy symptoms on sat august th and doc said it should be fine today spotting brown and went in for blood test to confirm my levels are so low right now and they said that i am in fact having a miscarriage its hard to hear but things could be worse its funny how attached you can get to something in such a short amount of time it is absolutely normal to feel sad i lost little angels at and weeks and i can tell you that my heart still ache the moment you get a positive result on a pregnancy test your heart beats faster you start making plans for the future you can almost see that baby in college you with out noticing start rearranging your life around that news and when a miscarriage happen you world come tumbling down a lot of people don't get the pain and the sorrow you can get through it and you will be stronger for it keep your head high and tell yourself that there is a little angel watching out for you up there Miscarriage Shaggy dog story Abortion The Inside Blood on the Tracks Obstetrics Pitaten Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Time Out of Mind Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Jon Secada Abortion debate Milton H. Erickson Prostate cancer Friends Theory of conduct Coeliac disease Childbirth EastEnders Polycystic ovary syndrome Endometriosis Knots Landing Oral contraceptive Slow Train Coming Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Clinical depression Anxiety